cts. Examples for technical scale processes and representative machinery used therein give insight into the technical reality of a dyehouse. A new chapter about circularity of textiles highlights the interlinkage between product design, including dyes and finishes, and the requirements to develop future fibre-to-fibre recycling. The work covers all relevant aspects of a textile product from fibre production, coloration, finishing, consumer use and fibre-to-fibre recycling. The content of the book allows a first entry into this multi-disciplinary field. Through its comprehensive character the authors explain the interdependence between textile and fibre processing and aspects of recycling, which makes the work a valuable source of information to design future textiles for circularity.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 4aFarbstoffe. 4aFaserchemie. 4aFärbung. 4aTextilfasern. 4aTextilforschung. 4aVeredelung. 4aZirkularität. 7aTechnology & Engineering / Textiles & Polymers.2bisacsh  a.  aCircularity.  aColoration.  aDyes.  aFibre Chemistry.  aFinishing.  aTextile Fibers.  aTextile Research.1 aPham, Tung, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z97831111757820 cEPUBz97831107957760 cprintz978311079569140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311079573840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110795738423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110795738/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  aEBA_CL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK